    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>Adding color support to a Drupal theme allows site owners/administrators to modify the theme's color scheme directly from a settings page, rather than having to edit any CSS.</p>
<p><span class="blog-img"><img src="http://mydrupalblog.lhmdesign.com/files/blogimg/designkit-color-schemes.png" alt="Drupal color schemes" /></span></p>
<p>I'm currently assessing color integration options for <a href="http://drupal.org/project/neptune">Neptune</a> and have found <a href="http://drupal.org/project/designkit">DesignKit</a> to be a quick, easy, and flexible alternative to <a href="https://drupal.org/node/108459">direct color module itegration</a> (as used by Garland and Bartik). On the flip side, there are a couple of caveats (see below).</p>
<p>This tutorial will focus on implementing basic color configuration, although DesignKit also supports image configuration and more advanced color configuration (including color blending/shifting).</p>
